# Offerly Development Guidelines

## Application Context
Mobile onboarding application built with React Native CLI, featuring multi-step form wizard and user authentication system.

## Core Technologies
| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|-------|------------|-------|
| Runtime | React Native CLI 0.74.x | TypeScript enabled |
| Routing | React Navigation v7 | native-stack navigator |
| State | Zustand + MMKV | Persistent storage |
| Forms | react-hook-form + zod | Schema validation |
| Motion | react-native-reanimated v3 | Custom animations only |
| Testing | Jest + RNTL | Unit + Integration |

## Directory Layout
```
src/
├── app/              # Bootstrap code
├── navigation/       # Route definitions
├── features/         # Screen modules
│   ├── onboarding/   # Wizard flow
│   └── authentication/
├── shared/           # Common components
│   ├── ui/           # Button, Input, etc.
│   └── onboarding/   # Step indicator
├── state/            # Global stores
├── lib/              # Helpers & schemas
├── design/           # Visual tokens
└── types/            # Type definitions
```

## Naming Standards
| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `AnimatedStepIndicator.tsx` |
| Stores | camelCase + use | `useOnboardingStore.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `schemas.ts` |
| Types | PascalCase | `OnboardingState` |

## Component Guidelines
- Functional components with typed props
- SafeAreaWrapper on all screens
- Keyboard handling for form inputs
- Accessibility labels required

## State Guidelines
- Zustand for app-wide state
- react-hook-form for form state
- MMKV persistence for draft data
- Clear data only after completion

## Animation Guidelines
- useSharedValue + useAnimatedStyle
- Prefer withSpring for natural feel
- UI thread execution (worklets)
- No third-party progress libraries

## Validation Guidelines
- Schemas in lib/schemas.ts
- Zod for type-safe validation
- Validate on blur + submit
- Inline error display

## Testing Guidelines
- Schema edge cases
- Store operations
- Navigation flows
- Mock native modules

## Quality Standards
- No `any` types
- Prefer const
- Early returns
- Functions < 50 lines
- DRY with hooks/utils

## Prohibited Patterns
- Class components
- AsyncStorage
- Pre-built progress bars
- Missing validation
- Excessive inline styles
- console.log in production
- TypeScript errors
